<i>adverb</i>: 확실히 [확씰히], 하릴없이 [하ː리럽씨], 필연코 [피련코], 필연 [피련], 필시 [필씨], 정녕코 [정녕코], 분명히 [분명히], 분명 [분명], 똑 [똑], 단연히 [다ː년히], 단연코 [다ː년코], 단단히 [단단히] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>확실히 [확씰히]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; confidently; definitely</dd><br>
<dd>실제와 꼭 같거나 틀림없이 그러하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being absolutely true or being certain of something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하릴없이 [하ː리럽씨]</dt><br>
<dd>1. helplessly</dd><br>
<dd>달리 어떻게 할 방법이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of having no choice but to do something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. certainly; surely; exactly</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 틀림이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Absolutely correct.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>필연코 [피련코]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; without fail</dd><br>
<dd>(강조하는 말로) 조금도 어긋나지 않고 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>(emphatic form) Certainly, without fail.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>필연 [피련]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; without fail</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 어긋나지 않고 반드시.</dd><br>
<dd>Certainly, without fail.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>필시 [필씨]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely</dd><br>
<dd>거의 어긋나는 일이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Almost without any doubt.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>정녕코 [정녕코]</dt><br>
<dd>at all; surely</dd><br>
<dd>(강조하는 말로) 정녕.</dd><br>
<dd>(emphasizing form) Really.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>분명히 [분명히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. clearly</dd><br>
<dd>모습, 소리 등이 흐릿하지 않고 또렷하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a clear appearance, sound, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. firmly</dd><br>
<dd>태도, 목표 등이 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Set on a clear attitude, goal, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. surely</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사실이 틀림이 없이 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>(a fact being confirmed) Certainly and accurately.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>분명 [분명]</dt><br>
<dd>clearly; surely</dd><br>
<dd>틀림없이 확실하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Clearly and surely.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>똑 [똑]</dt><br>
<dd>certainly; surely; exactly</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 틀림이 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Exactly right in every way.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단연히 [다ː년히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. obviously</dd><br>
<dd>순위나 수준, 정도 등이 확실히 판단이 될 만큼 뚜렷하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Obviously in deciding a rank, level, degree, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. surely</dd><br>
<dd>흔들리거나 망설이지 않고.</dd><br>
<dd>Without being shaken or hesitating.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단연코 [다ː년코]</dt><br>
<dd>1. obviously</dd><br>
<dd>순위나 수준, 정도 등이 확실히 판단이 될 만큼 뚜렷하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Obviously in deciding a rank, level, degree, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. by all means</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 경우에도 절대로.</dd><br>
<dd>Absolutely in whatever occasion.</dd><br>
<dd>3. surely</dd><br>
<dd>무슨 일이 있어도 꼭.</dd><br>
<dd>Surely, despite anything.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단단히 [단단히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. hard</dd><br>
<dd>사물이 어떤 힘에 의해 모양이 변하지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>(an object) Hard enough not to be changed by a certain force.</dd><br>
<dd>2. hard; solidly</dd><br>
<dd>약하거나 무르지 않고 빈틈이 없이 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Evenly solid, not weakly or softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. firmly</dd><br>
<dd>속이 꽉 차서 야무지고 실속이 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>Fully, firmly, and practically.</dd><br>
<dd>4. tightly; firmly</dd><br>
<dd>느슨하지 않고 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Strongly, not loosely.</dd><br>
<dd>5. surely; strongly</dd><br>
<dd>뜻이나 생각이 흔들림 없이 강하게.</dd><br>
<dd>(one's will or thought maintained) Strongly, without being shaken.</dd><br>
<dd>6. seriously; severely</dd><br>
<dd>보통보다 더 심하게.</dd><br>
<dd>More severely than normal.</dd><br>
<dd>7. surely</dd><br>
<dd>확실하게 제대로.</dd><br>
<dd>Done surely.</dd><br>
<dd>8. strongly</dd><br>
<dd>일의 기본 바탕이 튼튼하게.</dd><br>
<dd>(the ground for something made) Strongly.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>